<sect1 id="w3m" xreflabel="w3m-&w3m-version;">
  <?dbhtml filename="w3m.html"?>


  <title>W3m-&w3m-version;</title>

  <indexterm zone="w3m">
    <primary sortas="a-W3m">W3m</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduction to W3m</title>

    <para><application>w3m</application> is both a pager and a
    text-mode WWW browser. It can be used as a replacement for the BLFS TUI WWW
    browsers with support for images and other tags and divs.</para>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Package Information</bridgehead>
    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>Download: <ulink url="&w3m-download;"/></para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">W3m Dependencies</bridgehead>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Required</bridgehead>
    <para role="required">
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/general/gc.html">GC</ulink>
    </para>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Recommended</bridgehead>
    <para role="recommended">
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/x/imlib2.html">imlib2</ulink> and
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/x/x7lib.html">Xorg Libraries</ulink>
    </para>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Optional</bridgehead>
    <para role="optional">
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/x/gdk-pixbuf.html">gdk-pixbuf</ulink>,
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/general/gpm.html">GPM</ulink>, and
      <xref linkend="m17n"/>
    </para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of W3m</title>

    <para>Install <application>w3m</application> by running the following
    commands:</para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --prefix=/usr          \
            --sysconfdir=/etc      \
            --enable-image=fb,x11  \
            --with-imagelib=imlib2 &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>Now, as the &root; user:</para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install &amp;&amp;
install -vDm644  doc/{HISTORY,READ*,keymap.*,menu.*,*.html} \
             -t  /usr/share/doc/w3m-&w3m-version;</userinput></screen>
  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="commands">
    <title>Command Explanations</title>

    <para><parameter>--sysconfdir=/etc</parameter>: This parameter puts the
    configuration files in /etc.</para>

    <para><parameter>--enable-image=fb,x11</parameter>: This parameter enables
    image support for the framebuffer and X11.</para>

    <para><parameter>--with-imagelib=imlib2</parameter>: This parameter builds
    against the Imlib2 image library for image support.</para>

  </sect2>

